    Represents a single message, which is composed of one or more fragments (some of which may have multiple forms).

  • Classes in com.google.i18n.pseudolocalization.message used by com.google.i18n.pseudolocalization.message 
    Class and Description
    Message
    Represents a single message, which is composed of one or more fragments (some of which may have multiple forms).
    MessageFragment
    One fragment of a Message.
    MessageFragmentVisitor
    Visitor interface for visiting individual message fragments.
    MessageVisitor
    Visitor for a single Message.
    NonlocalizableTextFragment
    A MessageFragment which represents plain text that must not be localized -- this may include HTML markup, text added by other pseudolocalizers, etc.
    Placeholder
    A MessageFragment which reprsents a placeholder, a value to be filled in at runtime.
    TextFragment
    A MessageFragment which represents plain text to be localized (though it may contain markup, such as HTML).
    VariantForm
    One form of a VariantSelector.
    VariantFormVisitor
    A visitor for VariantForm instances.
    VariantFragment
    A MessageFragment which has multiple messages, chosen based on some parameters.
    VariantFragmentVisitor
    A visitor for visiting a VariantFragment.
    VariantSelector
    One selector in a VariantFragment, which chooses among variant forms based on a parameter value.
    VisitorContext
    Context around a MessageFragment that allows inserting, removing, and replacing nodes.
